title: DENON AVR-2307CI, 7.1 channel receiver w/ HDMI, XM, iPod, dd/dts-MINT
description:
For sale is my Denon AVR-2307CI, 7.1 Channel A/V home theater receiver with HDMI switching. The receiver is in near MINT condition both mechanically and cosmetically. It would be ideal as the heart of any home theater and/or music HIFI system. The AVR-2307CI incorporates very high power (100 watts per channel RMS) into all 7 channels that can easily power 5 to 7 speakers in a surround sound system. The Denon also has the surround sound technology you need, such as Dolby Pro Logic IIx decoding with Cinema and Music Modes, DTS Extended Surround Discrete 6.1 decoding, DTS Extended Surround Matrix 6.1 decoding, DTS Neo:6 Cinema & Music Surround decoding, Dolby Digital decoding, including Matrix 6.1 decoding. The Denon also has 2nd zone capability! With this important feature, you can be watching a movie in 5.1 surround sound in your main room while you have music playing in another room or the patio....at the same time! As many know, Denon is considered as one of the best in the business. 
 
1) Denon AVR-2307CI, Price is: $259.99 or best reasonable offer 
 
Original MSRP of the AVR-2307CI is $799.  
 
The unit comes with:   Denon remote control,  AM/FM antennas, set up microphone, and the owners manual. 
 
Please feel free to contact me at (call/text)  480-269-3eight37 to set up a time to audition the Denon. 
 
Denon's AVR-2307CI delivers a riveting home theater experience every time you turn it on. Armed with plenty of advanced surround processing capabilities and 100 watts per channel of muscular, high-current amplification, this receiver will drive up to seven speakers with power and precision. It's also loaded with features that expand your entertainment options -- including XM Radio and iPod integration -- plus others designed to optimize the sound of your system and streamline video connections.  
 
HDMI switching and video conversion 
The '2307CI's advanced digital video capability makes it easy to connect two HDMI-equipped video components and switch between them while maintaining the best possible picture quality for both. If you've got an HDTV with only one HDMI input, you'll really appreciate this handy feature. For even more convenience, analog-to-HDMI video conversion means this receiver can send all of your video sources to your compatible TV using only a single digital cable. And if you don't have a TV with a digital video input, the '2307's component video conversion still provides simplified switching for all your video sources.  
 
Sirius/XM Satellite Radio 
This receiver also helps you keep pace with changing trends in music listening. Just add an optional Sirius/XM Mini-Tuner package and an Sirius/XM subscription to enjoy instant access to more than 170 digital channels of music, news, talk, and sports. It's even compatible with Sirius/XM's new HD Surround channels, which deliver music in multichannel sound.  
 
iPod/iPhone integration 
Pick up an optional Denon ASD-1R control dock, and you can integrate your iPod into your home theater system. Listen to your digital music files through your best speakers and view your song titles, playlists, photos, and video on your TV. The dock even charges your iPod as it plays, and lets you control your player using the receiver's remote.  
 
Easy, accurate speaker setup 
Denon's Auto Setup and Room EQ Adjust takes the hassle out of speaker configuration. Just plug in the included microphone and place it in your favorite listening seat. The '2307CI then uses a series of test tones to balance speaker levels and fine-tune the delay and equalization settings for each speaker. The result is optimized home theater performance for your specific speakers and room.  
 
Versatility and convenience 
You get a multibrand remote with glow-in-the-dark keys for streamlined control of every component in your system, even in low lighting. The '2307CI's icon-based on-screen display puts receiver menus on your TV screen to simplify system setup and navigation. The handy front-panel optical digital input lets you easily connect a compatible game console to experience thrilling digital surround sound with your video games. And dual-room/dual-source capability lets you enjoy home theater in your main room while a housemate listens to music in another room. This receiver can even power stereo speakers in your second room.

RS-232 support means compatibility with the latest professional home automation systems from control leaders like Crestron and Control. And the VSX-30 brings extensive connectivity for your digital media via Ethernet and a front A/V input, and compatibility with Bluetooth sources (using the optional AS-BT100 adapter, sold separately). 
 
The Ultimate iPhone Experience--Now In Your Home Theater 
 
"Made for iPhone" Certification Provides iPhone Users the Ultimate Integration for their Home Theater 
Get a truly plug-and-play iPhone experience in your home theater. Thanks to the VSX-30's "Made for iPhone/iPod/iPad" certification, you can enjoy music with iTunes album art, movies, downloaded TV shows from iTunes, photos, web and more. An included USB/composite video cable makes connecting your iPhone to share your favorite media easy--and your iPhone charges automatically when connected. This included cable also works with most generations of iPod Classic, Nano, and iPod Touch. 
 
Share your videos, and enjoy music with full album information and album art on your TV. Your iPhone device's wireless and network features remain fully functional and music and movies will mute when you receive an incoming call. And you've got lots of control options--use the iPhone directly, or push a single button on the VSX-30's front panel to switch control to the included preset remote and an intuitive, full-color GUI. 
 
Pioneer's Free iPhone App Turns Your iPhone, iPad, or iPod touch into a Powerful Control Center 
Pioneer's iControlAV (a free download from Apple's App Store) gives you total control over your home theater sound. With controls for master and per-zone volume, sound fields, and more, you've got a simple but powerful way to adjust your home theater sound any way you like. 
 
The iPhone, iPad, and iPod touch device's accelerometer are used to control the balance, bass and dialogue--no confusing sequence of remote buttons to remember, just tilt and maneuver your Apple portable device until the sound is right where you want it. 
 
Where Maximum Fidelity Meets Connectivity 
 
Access Your Portable Devices, Internet Radio, and More 
In addition to connections for all your home theater components, a front USB port lets you connect your digital camera or portable media player to display a slideshow of JPEG photos on your HDTV, or play MP3, WAV, or WMA music files with full ID3 tag and album art support. Elite receivers will display up to 32 album art thumbnails on your TV, and you can scroll through them with the included remote. And your options don't stop with your portable devices. When connected to your home network, the VSX-30 is your portal for thousands of Internet radio stations -- all just a few clicks of the remote away. 
 
Full-Color On-Screen GUI 
There are more ways to control your Pioneer VSX-30 than just your iPhone. There's a full-color on-screen GUI for use with the included learning remote, so you can make guided adjustments to your home theater sound. Not only that, but all Elite receivers let you connect a USB keyboard so you can rename stations for radio and Internet radio, network settings, and more. 
 
Release Your Smartphone's Music with the AS-BT100 Bluetooth Adapter (sold separately) 
For wireless connectivity, add a Pioneer AS-BT100 Bluetooth adapter (sold separately) to release your music from your iPhone, iPad, Blackberry, or Android smartphone as well as other Bluetooth-enabled sources like laptops. It's a plug-and-play solution for listening to your smartphone's digital music library. And Pioneer's exclusive Sound Retriever AIR restores critical audio data that is often removed from compressed audio formats, especially when transferred via Bluetooth. 
 
 
How Pioneer's Technology Delivers the Ultimate Home Theater Experience 
 
The Latest HDMI Technology Gets You Ready for 3-D 
All of Pioneer's latest receivers support the latest HDMI 1.4a specification, meaning that you're not just getting the most out of your existing movies and music, you're preparing for the next generation of 3-D video content with the VSX-30. And with 4 HDMI inputs, you've got more than enough connectivity options for the growing number of high-definition sources available today. 
 
1080p Upscaling from Any Source 
Pioneer has long been the leader in video processing and the VSX-30 is no exception. Anchor Bay (VRS) Video Reference Series video processing lets you upscale your picture to digital 1080p from virtually any source, including analog. Additionally, 3D Noise Reduction and a suite of video adjustments ensure you'll get the best picture possible from anything you've got. 
 
True-to-Life, High-Definition Audio and New Dolby Pro Logic IIz 
Of course all the latest Pioneer receivers support high-definition audio formats like Dolby TrueHD and DTS-HD Master Audio to give your Blu-ray Disc movies a soundtrack that's true-to-life. But Pioneer adds an extra dimension with support for Dolby Pro Logic IIz across its entire 2010 line of receivers, which adds a "height" channel for an exciting new surround sound option. 
 
Near Studio-quality Sound with Advanced MCACC 
Pioneer's exclusive Multi-Channel Acoustic Calibration system (MCACC) provides a near studio-quality, multi-channel listening experience that customizes each of the VSX-30's 7.1 sound channels specifically to your listening environment. 
Additionally, the Auto Level Control feature can equalize volume level differences between tracks playing from a portable audio device or commercials during television programming so the volume can be enjoyed at a consistent level--no more jarring "blare" when switching audio sources. 
 
Where the VSX-30 truly shines is with custom control options. Full custom feature-sets including 2-zone Audio as well as partnerships with 3rd party controllers like Control4, Crestron and AMX ensure compatibility with the latest home automation technologies. 
 
All of these technologies come together in the VSX-30 to deliver an unprecedented level of control and sophistication for the serious home entertainment enthusiast.

title: 2004 Mercedes C230 Sport
description:
I bought this Mercedes a little over 2 years ago and put on less than 30k miles. It's been a great car and I am selling it just to purchase another car. It's been immaculately maintained. I have over $4000 in receipts from Noe Imports in Mesa. Mostly rubber and wear items. I just did the fuel sending unit about 2 months ago for $800. New motor and transmission mounts. All the hoses for the supercharger. New alternator pulley since the alternator had already been replaced. The previous owner had it maintained at Mercedes of Chandler. A new battery 3 months ago, the front 2 tires were replaced this summer with Goodyear Eagle GT's. and not not much before that the rears were new from Discount tire.  
There are no rips or tears in the leather. New front brakes about 11k miles ago.  
 
I also put in close to $2000 in stereo equipment. 7" JVC KW-V50BT Multimedia receiver. USB & HDMI ports. DVD player. 2 amps both digital. 1-4 channel JL Audio XD400/4 ( still a $400 amp ) and also a Alpine amp for the subs. Still has factory speakers. Bluetooth, Pandora, etc. You can also broadcast your iPhone to the screen and play movies, YouTube, or whatever on the screen.  I do still have the original factory stereo and amp if you don't care about the aftermarket stereo.  
 
The rear sunshade doesn't go down ( very common problem ). The motor is out. I purchased one and just never had it put in the car. It's normally a $1200 fix primarily for the shade.  
 
It's going to be due for plates in January. I think they were about $65 last year. 
 
I had it checked by Noe imports prior to purchase and they mentioned that there had been some body work on one of the rear corners. I couldn't tell. I have never had any accidents. The rubber around the drivers door is coming off and I priced it for $140 but just haven't done it.  
 
It's a well maintained, beautiful car worth seeing/driving. No oil leaks and I have the books and my records. No trades. Serious inquiries only!  
 
Someone actually stopped by my house after seeing it in my driveway and was interested in buying it about 7 months ago though I wasn't interested in selling at that time. 
 
**FYI** All Mercedes including used come with roadside assistance. You just need to call a dealer and have it changed.

title: Pioneer A1 WiFi speaker with AirPlay, DLNA, Spotify Connect
description:
Selling a great condition Pioneer XW-SMA1 (A1) speaker with built in WiFi. It also has ethernet for a wired connection, aux in, and USB (for audio through USB on iPhone including the jackless iPhone 7 and 7 Plus). It is large and has a great sound. 
 
This is a great and versatile speaker. It includes built in AirPlay for wirelessly streaming audio from your iOS, Mac, and iTunes, as well as DLNA, for streaming your local audio files in a more broadly support method. It also has Spotify Connect, which is Spotify's own wireless streaming system, which allows the speaker to connect directly to Spotify, allow you to use your phone as a remote, but free to do other things (versus AirPlay which streams from your phone to the speaker). 
 
Also a ton of wired options and an app that lets you stream Pandora and vTuner directly to the speaker, too. 
 
Note: This is not a Bluetooth speaker, and it is not portable. It needs to be plugged in, and uses WiFi for connection, which allows a better sound than Bluetooth. 
 
Includes all original accessories, including power adapter and remote control. 
 
Also selling the bigger, louder Pioneer A4 speaker. It is identical to this in features, but packs a bigger sound. Also includes all original stuff. Selling A4 for $120. Both A1 and A4 together for $160.

title: Brand NEW!! Martin Logan Montis ( RESERVE SERIES with 5 year WARRANTY!
description:

The Montis arrived via Pilot Freight on 12/22/2016 and  I currently have them hooked up to a Mcintosh Mc402 amplifier, This combo is just Magical! title: 2015 Chevy Malibu LT
description:
I have a 2015 Chevrolet Malibu for sale, It is in excellent condition, Only has 18500 miles on it,  
 
MyLink and OnStar with 4G LTE details 
Malibu's next-generation MyLink gives customers the best of both worlds when it 
comes to infotainment. It provides easy, intuitive operation of basic functions, yet it 
is also highly customizable and capable of linking up to 10 devices such as 
smartphones, SD cards and MP3 players, giving users more ways of staying 
connected. It is standard on LT and LTZ models. 
Enhanced connectivity and convenience include a new Text Messaging Alerts 
feature for smartphone users with Bluetooth profile (M.A.P.), which reads incoming 
texts through the vehicle's speakers, and Siri Eyes Free for iPhone iOS 6 and iOS 7 
users to enhance connectivity and convenience. Each enables voice-controlled 
connectivity, to help keep phones safely stored and hands on the wheel.  
 
Additional standard and available features include: 
 Eight-inch-diagonal color touch screen and multiple USB ports 
 Enhancements including gesture recognition and natural language voice 
recognition 
 
Designed for safety 
Malibu offers a wide range of standard and available safety features in the segment. 
Available side blind zone alert and rear cross traffic alert complement the available 
forward collision alert and lane departure warning to enhance Malibu's crashavoidance 
capability. These advanced, active technologies use radar to help avoid 
crashes, with visual and audible alerts designed to identify potential threats with 
sufficient warning to give the driver time to react and make changes. They're part 
of the segment's only suite of advanced safety technologies offered on a midlevel 
trim. 
Additional contributors to Malibu's safety and peace of mind include 10 standard air 
bags -- and two optional air bags -- and available rear vision camera. The standard 
and available air bags include: 
 Dual-stage driver and front passenger air bags (two) 
 Pelvic/thorax side-impact air bags for all outboard occupants, front and rear 
(four) 
 Driver and passenger knee air bags (two)• Roof rail air bags with rollover protection (two) 
Available second-row head/thorax side-impact air bags (two). 
Malibu also employs systems that enable greater vehicle control, including standard 
StabiliTrak electronic stability control system, all-speed traction control and fourwheel 
disc brakes with four-channel ABS. 
OnStar is standard. It uses GPS and cellular phone technology to automatically call 
for help in the event of crash. OnStar service also includes MyLink mobile apps, 
which offer vehicle information and OnStar services via the customer's smartphone. 
 
Stop/start technology enhances efficiency 
 The stop/start feature shuts down the engine in certain driving conditions to 
reduce fuel consumption. Along with other technologies, including direct injection, 
variable valve lift control and a six-speed automatic transmission, the 2.5L 
powertrain contributes to EPA-estimated fuel economy ratings of 25 mpg in city 
driving and 36 mpg on the highway. 
There are no buttons to push or procedures to learn with Malibu's stop/start 
system. It automatically shuts down the engine when the car comes to a stop under 
certain driving conditions, such as a stoplight. The engine automatically restarts 
when the driver takes his or her foot off the brake. The system monitors vehicle 
speed, climate control system operation and other factors to determine whether it 
is efficient to shut off the engine.  
 
The 2.5L is SAE-certified at 196 horsepower (146 kW) and 186 lb-ft of torque (252 
Nm). Revised transmission shift points and quicker shifts also enhance the feeling 
of performance -- while delivering greater refinement.

title: 1984 Grady White Sailfish 255 Repowered 4Strokes
description:
I have a 25ft Grady White that the wife says I have to get rid of.  It's an older boat but maintained meticulously.  It has a 9'6" beam which is the biggest you tow.  It was repowered in 2003 with dual Yamaha F200TXR 4 Stroke outboard engines.  Both engines have 890 + or - 5 hours.  Comes with a Simrad / Lowrance NSS9 Evo 2 Multi Function Display, 4G radar (best radar on the market), Side Scan LSS1 transducer, TM150 Chirp transducer. Simrad Autopilot, and Simrad RS32 VHF Rado that is networked into the system to allow for DSC, dual channel AIS, and GPS.  These are the best electronics on the market.  Comes loaded with Navionics map updated this year and all my fish waypoints.   
Inside the cabin has a sink with fresh water, head or toilet that can double as a shower, a v birth that sleeps 2-3 and a small bunk that fits one comfortably.  Some of the other features are: 
 
 
 
The bad: 
 
1. Eisenglass on port side is worn and just zip tied to the t-top. 
2. Trailer has a couple center rollers missing.  The boat doesn't need them because it sits on the bunks but adding the two rollers (about $25 for both) would make the trailer complete. 
3. Bottom paint is intact but could use a fresh coat. 
 
This boat is an offshore fishing machine.  Range is about 300 miles depending on seas.  Can sea trial boat with proof of funds.  The  engines run like a top and never had any problems.  Lower unit oil changed every couple months.  Oil change, thermostats, and oil filters just changed this week.  I wish more then anything I could keep this boat. The engines alone are worth $20k.  $30000 is firm and I will take nothing less. 
If interested, please call or text me at

All 100% done right and professionally. Debuted in 2012 SEMA show for BMS Off-road (Blitzkerg) as their feature. This is a very hard truck to find and a great foundation to continue building upon if wanted.  
 
It's set up perfect, as it rides very smooth and quite inside. The suspension was valved appropriately for the weight of the truck and rear end was built to handle the extra rotating mass. Tows a 20'+ Trailer w/two razors with no hesitation too. The engine internals were left un-touched for reliability, as the bolt on performance was professionally tuned in as well.  
 
I'm sorry but I'm not parting out and/or looking for trades. There way too much to list and explain on this little ad. The iPhone pics don't do this truck any justice, it's a must see in person. My truck is located at my house in Arizona but registered to my other residence in Anchorage, AK. Something has come up financially, so if you're a serious buyer just text/call me at a decent time for more info please. My name is Rocky

description:
Why Cellulose Insulation?  
 
1. It Saves You Money!

5. Performs better in a fire than even fiberglass

1. Includes Installation, Basic Delivery, and Labor  
2. Green Cellulose Insulation to cover a 2-car attic (up to 540 sq. ft. at R-19)  
3. Insulate the back of your attic door  
4. Inspect your attics ventilation  
5. Insulating your garage attic can make your garage more comfortable  
6. $399 for 3-Car garage (up to 810 sq. ft. at R-19) 
  
 _______________________________________ 
 
$249 2-Car Garage Door Insulation  
1. Includes Installation, Basic Delivery**, and Labor  
2. Single-car garage door insulation  
3. Plastic laminated for professional look  
4. Keeps your garage much cooler.  
5. Very lightweight, we adjust garage door opener  
6. 2-car and 1-car insulation $379  
 
________________________________________________________________________  
 
Tired of your HIGH Arizona Electric Bills? Do something about it. 
 
The photos show a typical Arizona attic with just a couple of inches of insulation and how we brought it up to current standards.  
The other photo shows how Thermal Imaging reveals missing insulation.  
 
Electric Prices are only going one direction and that's UP! They want another 10.9% increase now. By adding insulation, a programmable thermostat, CFL lighting, and doing some simple maintenance you can cut your energy bills by 30% or more. This year do something about it by calling us today for a free quote and beat the SUMMER HEAT! You probably have been CHEATED according to Home Energy Magazine. Most of the attics I have seen in Arizona are severely deficient in insulation, even newer homes, and especially homes with remodeling and additions. http://homeenergy.org/archive/hem.dis.anl.gov/eehem/00/001112.html . Read the article, then have us come out for a free inspection of your attic, complete with a thermal imaging camera.  
 
A framer, electrician, pest control guy, A/C repair guy, cable / satellite guy, roofer, butcher, baker, and candlestick maker have all been trampling your attic insulation. Even newer homes with the parade of trades doing warranty work have compromised the effectiveness of your insulation. It is common to find bare spots where the wind has blown away your insulation or the original installer short changed you. Call us today and get your home ready for Arizona and a greener electric bill. You will save on your electric as well as providing a more comfortable home.  
 
You know there is a problem with your insulation. Do Something About It! Let us provide the materials for you or we can install cheaper than you can buy the materials at the big box stores. If you ask an A/C guy why is your house so hot; he will tell you your air conditioner is undersized, blame it on the builder, and write up a $7,000 fix. He has seen your attic and knows you only have 3-4" of insulation, but he doesn't make money on insulation. Let us take a look at your attic, if it has enough insulation and it is complete, we will tell you. If it needs work we will provide expert advice and provide you with options to fit your budget.  
 
 
Most times, the access to the attic blocked by your couch, crib, bowflex, treadmill, bed, air compressor, generator, washer, dryer, recliner, desk, iphone, Picasso, windows, computer, cat, camera, diamond ring, refrigerator, microwave, dining room table, and grandmothers oxygen tank. We will very gently help you move any items necessary, but are not responsible for any damage unless it is due to negligence. We cannot help you move your boat, trailer, motorcycle, quads, plasma / lcd / tube TV, bodily fluids, nuclear devices, or land shark dog. All we need to enter the attic is a person and a hose. The machine is often left on the truck street-side or just outside the garage.  
We are not a Handy Man service.  
 
__________________________________________________________________________

o Free Basic Delivery to Metro Phoenix, Peoria, Glendale, Paradise Valley, Avondale, Goodyear, Surprise.

title: ATTIC INSULATION
description:
Why Cellulose Insulation?  
 
1. It Saves You Money!  
2. It is made from 85% recycled material.  
3. No-Itch like fiberglass  
4. Provides an even seamless blanket of protection from the heat and cold  
5. Performs better in a fire than even fiberglass  
6. The only thing we take to the attic is a hose to install. If you want to do it yourself, we are cheaper than the big box stores on bags.  
 __________________________________________  
$12 per bag -- Contractor size bags of Cellulose Insulation. Each bag contains 55% more material than a $11 bag at Lowes. It's the same material, just a huge SAVINGS! 
(2) free premium dust masks with any order over 20 bags.   
 
1. Do-It-Yourself. Does not include Installation, Tax, or Delivery

 __________________________________________  
 
$599 "Craigslist Special" Insulation Upgrade Pack (65% off of Home Depot's installed price)  
 
1. 6" R-19 Blown-in Cellulose Topper, up to 1500 sq. ft.  
2. Includes Installation, Delivery and Labor  
3. Level out Bare Spots, Gaps, and Voids  
4. Insulate the back of your attic door  
5. Inspect your attics ventilation  
6. Standard attic access required  
7. Modest fuel surcharge may apply  
8. For homes larger than 1500 sq. ft. call for custom quote  
9. Upgrade to 9" R-30 topper for $849, 12" R-38 topper for $1099  
 
__________________________________________  
 
 
$299 - Garage Attic Insulation  
1. Includes Installation, Basic Delivery, and Labor  
2. Green Cellulose Insulation to cover a 2-car attic (up to 540 sq. ft. at R-19)  
3. Insulate the back of your attic door  
4. Inspect your attics ventilation  
5. Insulating your garage attic can make your garage more comfortable  
6. $399 for 3-Car garage (up to 810 sq. ft. at R-19) 
  
 _______________________________________ 
 
$249 2-Car Garage Door Insulation  
1. Includes Installation, Basic Delivery**, and Labor  
2. Single-car garage door insulation  
3. Plastic laminated for professional look  
4. Keeps your garage much cooler.  
5. Very lightweight, we adjust garage door opener  
6. 2-car and 1-car insulation $379  
 
________________________________________________________________________  
 
Tired of your HIGH Arizona Electric Bills? Do something about it. 
 
The photos show a typical Arizona attic with just a couple of inches of insulation and how we brought it up to current standards.  
The other photo shows how Thermal Imaging reveals missing insulation.  
 
Electric Prices are only going one direction and that's UP! They want another 10.9% increase now. By adding insulation, a programmable thermostat, CFL lighting, and doing some simple maintenance you can cut your energy bills by 30% or more. This year do something about it by calling us today for a free quote and beat the SUMMER HEAT! You probably have been CHEATED according to Home Energy Magazine. Most of the attics I have seen in Arizona are severely deficient in insulation, even newer homes, and especially homes with remodeling and additions. http://homeenergy.org/archive/hem.dis.anl.gov/eehem/00/001112.html . Read the article, then have us come out for a free inspection of your attic, complete with a thermal imaging camera.  
 
A framer, electrician, pest control guy, A/C repair guy, cable / satellite guy, roofer, butcher, baker, and candlestick maker have all been trampling your attic insulation. Even newer homes with the parade of trades doing warranty work have compromised the effectiveness of your insulation. It is common to find bare spots where the wind has blown away your insulation or the original installer short changed you. Call us today and get your home ready for Arizona and a greener electric bill. You will save on your electric as well as providing a more comfortable home.  
 
You know there is a problem with your insulation. Do Something About It! Let us provide the materials for you or we can install cheaper than you can buy the materials at the big box stores. If you ask an A/C guy why is your house so hot; he will tell you your air conditioner is undersized, blame it on the builder, and write up a $7,000 fix. He has seen your attic and knows you only have 3-4" of insulation, but he doesn't make money on insulation. Let us take a look at your attic, if it has enough insulation and it is complete, we will tell you. If it needs work we will provide expert advice and provide you with options to fit your budget.  
 
 
Most times, the access to the attic blocked by your couch, crib, bowflex, treadmill, bed, air compressor, generator, washer, dryer, recliner, desk, iphone, Picasso, windows, computer, cat, camera, diamond ring, refrigerator, microwave, dining room table, and grandmothers oxygen tank. We will very gently help you move any items necessary, but are not responsible for any damage unless it is due to negligence. We cannot help you move your boat, trailer, motorcycle, quads, plasma / lcd / tube TV, bodily fluids, nuclear devices, or land shark dog. All we need to enter the attic is a person and a hose. The machine is often left on the truck street-side or just outside the garage.  
We are not a Handy Man service.

title: HAND-PRIMED, EXPERTLY CAMOUFLAGED BUGOUT Gamma Seal Lids & Buckets!!
description:
HAND-PRIMED, EXPERTLY CAMOUFLAGED BUGOUT Gamma Seal Lids & Buckets!! 
 
*** These Buckets and Lids are for SERIOUS Survivalists and/or Preppers, Hunters - ONLY! *** 
 
*** The photos that were taken during sundown, amongst the bushes, were taken on my iPhone at the last moment before I brought them home just after I had finished Re-Priming and Painting them (as mentioned below). I made no attempt whatsoever, to hide them! Those photos were only taken to give a serious buyer an idea of what they look like among some common desert shrubbery. *** 
 
I have 12, personally Primed (Ultra-Flat Black) and Camouflaged (Ultra-Flat Sand and Green) 5-gallon Buckets AND Gamma Seal Lids for sale. They are ideal for airtight and watertight situations where you must keep food, tools, large stocks of toilet paper, guns & ammo -- ANYTHING you can get into a 5-gal Bucket -- for safe, dry and airtight keeping at your camping, hunting or BUGOUT spots! 
 
I'm selling my Buckets and Lids as listed below: 
* * * For quantities of 1-5, $25. ea. * * * 
* * * For quantities of 6-10, $22.50 ea. * * *  
* * * To purchase all 12 Buckets and Lids, $240. ($20. ea) * * * 
 
For comparison's sake, I've made available, the following two links to Amazon.com's Black Gamma Seal LIDS ONLY -- "NOT BUCKETS!" (Although only some of my Buckets came from Home Depot, they happened to be the cheapest Bucket I could find on the Internet for comparison purposes, at about $3. ea, including tax.) 
  
Gamma Seal Lids on Amazon -- Black, 12-pk, $102 (PLUS approx. 7% tax) = $119., or $9. ea. (ADD an additional $3, minimum ea, for the cost of the Bucket/s themselves = $12. per Lid AND Bucket.) 
https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00S59JYU0/ref=s9_acsd_hps_bw_c_x_2_w 
 
The purchase price of one Gamma Seal Lid at-a-time on Amazon is $14.87 (PLUS approx. 7% tax) = almost  $16. ea. (ADD an additional $3, minimum ea, for the cost of the Bucket/s themselves = $19. per Lid AND Bucket.) 
https://www.amazon.com/Gamma2-4123-Gamma-Seal-Lid/dp/B0089QJQTS 
__________________________________________ 
 
* * * * Purchasing my entire stock of 12 (one-dozen) professionally Primed and Camouflaged Buckets and Gamma Seal Lids, you'll be paying less than $8 more per Bucket/Lid, than the UNprimed and UNpainted Amazon 12-pk of "Lids ONLY" offer above!!! (Did I mention that that's "LIDS ONLY" -- NO BUCKETS?) * * * * 
 
IF YOU FEEL MY PROFESSIONALLY HAND-PRIMED and CAMOUFLAGED 5-GAL BUCKETS and GAMMA-SEAL LIDS ARE NOT GREAT BARGAIN, PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING . . . 
___________________________________________ 
 
If you're in the market for well-primed and painted 5-gal Buckets and Gamma Seal Lids that you're able to store outside and not lose a minute's sleep wondering if they're safely "hidden" well enough to be left out in the elements for months (or longer) at-a-time, then look no further!  
 
If you're looking for tried-and-true, air and watertight, Professionally Camouflaged Buckets and Gamma Seal Lids that can be easily hidden in "plain sight," today's your VERY lucky day!! (If you had any idea of how much TIME and MONEY I've put into those suckers, you'd understand why I said ". . . today's your 'VERY' lucky day!") I've used some of these Buckets in the desert over the years -- in a number of diverse situations, elevations and grades, flora, foliage, shrubbery and climates, and they've never let me down!! On a number of occasions, I've even left some of these Buckets "hidden" for close to a year in such a perfect way with regards to keeping them out of the sun as much as possible -- AND out of the view of PEOPLE'S WANDERING EYES as they traverse the trail just 25' away. Never once have they ever failed me with regard to being dry inside and watertight, and especially for not ever being discovered by anyone!  
 
I started out by giving each Bucket and Lid's exterior surfaces a quick, rough sanding by hand with 60-grit sandpaper. Doing so takes off some of the gloss of the plastic, while preparing a much more suitable surface for the Ultra-Flat Black Primer to adhere to. 
 
I also Primed (and painted) the bottoms of each Bucket in the event they get turned over for some reason! I once had a couple of my Buckets turned over and scratched-up a bit by coyotes. (No, they didn't even come close to getting inside the Buckets, nor did they harm them in any way other than having to touch-up the scratch marks.) 
  
The next step, Priming each Bucket/Lid with an Ultra-Flat Black Primer, is an important step for several reasons: 
 
1)	Priming with an Ultra-Flat Black paint prepares the Buckets/Lids for the additional coats of Ultra-Flat paint. The Primer is the 'glue,' if you will, between the Bucket and the upcoming Ultra-Flat topcoats. Even with my heavy-grit sanding of all large surfaces of the Buckets and Lids, I can assure you that the top coats of paint will never stick to the Buckets/Lids without Priming them, first! (I tried. It doesn't work . . . :) 
2)	Priming the Buckets and Lids act to "de-gloss" the Buckets/Lids' glossy finish, thus "removing" the Buckets/Lids' glossy exterior finish. From YEARS of desert backpacking, hiking and living experience, I promise you, the first thing that's going to catch the eye of someone you don't want bothering your Buckets, is any sheen, shine or sunny reflection coming from your Buckets -- not necessarily how perfect the final Camouflaged job was! It's that shiny thing gleaming from the never-ending Valley sunlight that someone sees from 50-yards away, and is determined to check it out! Guess what, your site has just been exploited! 
 
Priming with Ultra-Flat Black is one of the most important steps in producing well-Camouflaged Buckets and Lids that you could otherwise only partially camouflage with nearby scrub brush, etc., or only partially bury -- or blend into a mountainous/rocky area. These Buckets are READY TO BE PLACED IN YOUR BUGOUT or "camping" AREA RIGHT NOW!! All you have to do is purchase a can or two of the Ultra-Flat final coat/s of paint you'll need to apply (if any) to have them blend into their environment.   
 
3)	Ultra-Flat Black Primer also gives you the best "primary" color there is for the initial covering of the Buckets/Lids. For instance, whatever you don't happen to cover with the natural colors (ALWAYS with Ultra-Flat Camouflage!) of the environment you're placing them, the Ultra-Flat Black will ALWAYS come through as a potential shadow. There is almost nowhere in the untouched desert that doesn't have a wide range and variety of rocks, scrub brush and cactus of all sizes, that all produce shadows at one point or another during the day. Chances are, if you're interested in placing these Buckets and Lids outdoors for any length of time, you'd have a much better chance of them not being discovered if you blended them into some brush, such in the outdoor desert photos I included. Once you do that, that Ultra-Flat Black Primer "bleeding through" your top-coats will be very much appreciated! 
 
4)	Another advantage of having the Ultra-Flat Black as a primary color is that it can be easily covered in any other ULTRA-FLAT CAMOUFLAGE paint colors ahead of placing them where you want to store/hide them -- incorporating the color/s of the environment you're placing them in -- then, with a can or two of your top-coat colors with you, you can touch-up your Buckets on-site if necessary. It's so simple, and works so well! You can even pull a plant/leaves and holding them up to the Buckets, spray paint over them, leaving a perfectly good reproduction of the vegetation surrounding your Buckets! (Practice on some newspaper, first! But even if you do make mistakes on your Buckets, it's simple and quick to re-paint and start over. 
 
I personally generally used Ultra-Flat "Sand" and/or a little Ultra-Flat "Light Green" on my Buckets. You can purchase these Ultra-Flat spray paint colors and more at Wal-Mart (cheapest), Ace hardware stores, etc. Wal-Mart is not only the cheapest -- but more importantly -- they almost always have a better selection and stock of the "Ultra-Flat Camouflage" spray paint colors, than anywhere else I've shopped. Please understand that IT MUST, MUST, MUST BE AN "'ULTRA-FLAT' CAMOUFLAGE" SPRAY PAINT FOR THIS TO WORK; NOTHING ELSE!!!  
_________________________________________ 
 
****** PLEASE DO NOT GET MY CAMOUFLAGED BUCKETS AND GAMMA-SEAL LIDS CONFUSED WITH THOSE RIDICULOUS, SO-CALLED "CAMOUFLAGED HUNTER BUCKETS" or ANY other so-called Camouflaged Buckets you come across -- IF ANY! They're as useless as tits on a bore-hog! WHY? Though, yes, technically, they are "camouflaged," yet the glossy finish of these Buckets renders them, well, "useless" - and a huge, dead giveaway to your goods! Can you afford to take that chance?! Again, all it takes is the Arizona sun glaring down on that shiny bucket, and not only could Joe Blow, the hiker see it, but if you happened to be on Federal property, such as - let's say the Tonto National Forest - you could be in a WORLD OF HURT if your local, FRIENDLY Law Enforcement Officer from the U.S. Park Rangers found it!! ;)  
 
If you're looking for Buckets you wish to house your heavy supplies in, including tools, food, handguns, ammo, etc., and not to have to haul back-and-forth to your vehicle, house, tent, cabin every day because you're worried they'll be stolen if you don't, these could be your answer. If you're going to leave supplies in your camping, BUGOUT or hunting area for a day or two or longer, my Buckets are the ONLY ones to trust! 
 
This is one of the few times when "used" is a good thing! They're all well-seasoned and battle-tested in real-world situations!! And for this sale, I just finished lightly re-sanding, completely re-Priming with Ultra-Flat Black Primer, and then -- again -- re-coating with Ultra-Flat "Light Green" and Ultra-Flat "Sand." That process alone took me 8-hours to accomplish, and cost me over $35.     **** Understand that that $35 is a drop-in-the-bucket (no pun intended:) compared to the amount of money I've invested in these and other Buckets over the past several years, Priming and top-coating most of them a number of times. ****  These extra layers of Ultra-Flat Primer and Ultra-Flat top-coats also add important extra levels of weather and water proofing, as well!  
 
Despite my best efforts to keep the Buckets' paint from chipping, it is virtually impossible -- especially when they're bouncing around in the back of a pick-up, or even when just carrying to your site if the Buckets are clanking on something hard (such as when carrying two Buckets at the same time in the same hand:). I was aware of this years ago, and quickly learned to always have a half-empty can of Ultra-Flat "Something" on hand for minor touch-ups.  
 
Hands-down, however, the main reason the Buckets flake or chip paint, is because THEY'RE ROUND. They don't have just four corners to be concerned about -- the entire Bucket IS A CORNER, per se. If you've ever noticed a piece of furniture, etc., it will always chip or wear-down the finish the most, on all of the corners; the "hard" edges -- the same edges and surfaces that will most likely get nicked and scraped when moving around. Now imagine an item such as the Buckets, that have no edges, as the ENTIRE Bucket IS AN EDGE!  
 
The bottom line is to not worry about trying to keep them scratch-free when filling and/or transporting them to your camping, hunting or BUGOUT spot. That's why I recommend to always sure to carry a have half-can or so of your dominant color (final coat) OR Flat-Black Primer with you. There are truly only a few places where they'll chip, so it's NOT necessary to carry around several cans of paint to do such little touching-up! 
 
Again, I'm selling my Buckets and Lids as listed below: 
* * * For quantities of 1-5, $25. ea. * * * 
* * * For quantities of 6-10, $22.50 ea. * * *  
* * * To purchase all 12 Buckets and Lids, $240. ($20. ea) * * * 
 
Just a heads-up: if you're contemplating going out and buying all of the materials you'd need to properly camouflage some buckets and Gamma Seal Lids in an effort to save money since you now have my tried-and-true method of creating the perfectly camouflaged bucket, give it up. I can tell you without hesitation, that you'll probably spend more per-bucket than what I am selling mine for - even at the "1-5, $25. ea" price, before you (maybe) get it right. Not to mention the enormous amount of time you will invest running around looking for exactly the right paints, then getting home (or wherever you don't want LOTS of overspray to come to a rest), and starting to experiment on the buckets and lids. It's expensive, both dollar- and time-wise. Plus, no offense, they won't be quite as effective as mine are. :-) 
 
Thanks for taking the time to checkout my Camouflaged Buckets & Gamma Seal Lids!!!

title: Denon AVR-X1000 network receiver, 3D HDMI, 4k, AirPlay/Pandora/Spotify
description:
For sale is my Denon AVR-X1000 A/V home theater receiver. The AVR-X1000 is a 5.1 channel (7.1 capable with pre outs) home theater receiver with an amazing array of features including HDMI (6 inputs, 1 output) and iPod/iPhone/iPad/Android compatibility via USB input.   Also supports streaming services such as Pandora, Spotify, and Sirius/XM satellite radio. 
 
The Denon would be ideal as the heart of any home theater and/or music HIFI system. The AVR-X1000 incorporates high power at 110 watts per channel @ 6 ohms that can easily power 5 speakers in a surround sound system. The X1000 is loaded with surround sound technology including several versions of Dolby Digital, Pro Logic IIz, and dts. Of course, the latest versions, Dolby Digital Plus, Dolby TrueHD and DTS-HD Master Audio decoding are on board as well. Finally, the X1000 also has 2nd zone capability when using an outboard 2 channel amplifier. This great feature allows you to watch a movie in full 5.1 surround sound in your main room while someone else enjoys 2 channel music in another room or patio....at the same time! 
 
1) Denon AVR-X1000 , Price is: $229.99 
 
 
Original MSRP of the AVR-X1000 is $599.  
 
Please call/text me at 48zero-269-383seven if interested in the Denon. 
 
The receiver comes with the: Denon remote control, am/fm antennas, and the owners manual (ec). 
 
Below is information on the X1000 pulled off the Denon website:  
 
High-res audio 
Make your network a home theater component 
Take your home theater beyond Blu-ray discs and CDs. Bring streaming music into the mix with the Denon AVR-X1000 IN-Command receiver. With network capability and Apple AirPlay, the 'X1000 makes it easy to enjoy digital tunes through your stereo or surround sound speakers. And thanks to Denon's knack for accurate sound, you can expect all your music and movies to come to life with detail and depth. 
 
Smart phone control 
The free Denon Remote app for Apple and Android lets you easily control the 'X1000 from your smartphone. 
 
Denon AVR-X1000 5.1-channel home theater receiver with Apple AirPlay 
Stream music from your iPad, iPhone, or computer running iTunes with the AVR-X1000's built-in AirPlay support. 
Stream easy with AirPlay 
 
Whether you've got music stored on your iPhone®, iPad®, or computer running iTunes®, AirPlay makes it as simple as pressing "Play" to stream songs to the 'X1000. It's so easy to browse and listen, you may find yourself rediscovering music you forgot you owned. Even if you don't have hundreds of gigabytes of digital tunes, don't feel left out -- the 'X1000 features built-in support for Spotify® and SiriusXM subscribers, as well as free Pandora® Internet radio and DLNA-compatibility for networked PCs. That's millions of songs at your fingertips before you've connected a single component to this receiver. AirPlay requires a wireless home network and a wired connection between the receiver and network. 
 
Audyssey fine-tunes your system 
 
Denon's home theater receivers continue to get easier to set up and control. One of the 'X1000's best setup features is the built-in Audyssey speaker calibration software. Not only does it optimize your system to fit your room, but it can also tone down loud commercials as well as improve dialogue and surround effects during low-level listening. The 'X1000's full-color on-screen display uses lots of graphics makes these and other settings a breeze to navigate. Once you're set up, be sure to download the free Denon Remote app for your Apple or Android™ smartphone. It's the simplest and most intuitive way to control your receiver via your home Wi-Fi network. 
 
Denon AVR-X1000 5.1-channel home theater receiver with Apple AirPlay 
The free Denon Remote app for Apple and Android lets you easily control the 'X1000 from your smartphone. 
Make a connection (or six) 
 
The 'X1000's connections can take on a wide variety sources. Six HDMI inputs offer plenty of versatility for Blu-ray players, game consoles, and cable boxes, with one front-panel input that's perfect for cameras or camcorders. There's also a front-panel USB connection for your iPod or other Apple device. It creates a direct digital connection, so you can get even better sound from it using the 'X1000's circuitry. 
 
Product Highlights: 
 
Power and Processing: 
 
5-channel amplifier 
110 watts per channel @ 1 kHz, 6 ohms 
80 watts per channel into 8 ohms (20-20,000 Hz) at 0.08% THD, with 2 channels driven 
Dolby® and DTS® surround sound decoding 
Audyssey "Silver" speaker calibration and system optimization includes: 
MultEQ® XT auto setup and room calibration delivers balanced, dynamic sound with enhanced surround performance for as many as eight seating positions 
Dynamic Volume anticipates loud sounds to keep volume levels even 
Dynamic EQ improves dialogue, bass response, and surround channel levels at lower volumes 
Digital and Streaming Music Options: 
 
Internet-ready for listening to music from a networked PC, free Internet radio, and music services 
includes support for Spotify, Pandora, and SiriusXM (subscription required for some services) 
Apple AirPlay for streaming music from an iPhone, iPad, iPod touch® or computer running iTunes 
plays high-resolution digital music files via USB storage device or a networked computer (up to 24-bit/192kHz resolution)

dual-room/dual-source output

using line-level Zone 2 output requires the use of separate amplifier or powered speakers

Pure Direct mode turns off unused circuitry for cleaner audio signals 
Denon's Compressed Audio Restorer improves sound quality of MP3s and other digital music files 
192kHz/24-bit digital-to-analog converters for all channels
